description: As the Hulk's long-lost son Hiro-Kala rockets towards us across the solar system, Steve Rogers and the Secret Avengers face a much more immediate threat -- three tons of Incredible Hulks cutting loose right here on Planet Earth! Forced to choose between his son and his planet, whose side will the Hulk take? And how will that affect his fragile bonds with his savage son Skaar and his even more savage wife, the Red She-Hulk? No one can save you like your family. But no one can drive you crazier. And when you're talking about a family of Hulks, it's that second part that makes the whole world tremble in fear. Written by "Planet Hulk" scribe Greg Pak and featuring the Hulk debut of fan favorite penciller Barry Kitson. PLUS: the first two installments of the S.M.A.S.H. FILES, secret stories of the Incredible Hulks!
name: Dark Son Part Three: Blast Off

description: The Book of the Black is pried open once more to reveal the untold horrors that occurred during BLACKEST NIGHT as guided by Sinestro Corps member Lyssa Drak. Be witness as swarms of Black Rings scavenge for souls within the tatters of Ragman! Cringe as Scarecrow bathes in the fear he constructs as a newly minted Sinestro Corpsman! Scream as Donna Troy transforms into a Black Lantern! Squirm as Animal Man literally feels his world – and himself – die! It's the emotional spectrum at its darkest in one special standalone issue!
name: Sea of Fear; The Evolution of Species; A Losing Battle; Blackest Nightmare; An Incident On Korugar

description: A standalone story in which a young man who happens upon a demented but beautiful woman, sealed away in a cage in the middle of the woods, only to be seduced into her erotic musings.
name: Manna

description: The series ends in a standalone tale in which a young man brings Whiskey home, and it leads to torrid and frenzied sexual activity.
name: Whiskey on a Sunday

volume.name: Luscious: The Collected Art of Al Rio

description: Originally issued as a prequel to the Sunglasses After Dark mini-series, this issue is the first comic book appearance of Sonja Blue and contains story and art not available anywhere else.

name: Operaciòn Tokio Japòn con Titina Romàn

description: More than one thousand years before Luke Skywalker, a dark age grips the galaxy as an ineffectual Republic abandons entire systems to Sith control. A newly knighted Jedi on her first mission, eighteen-year-old Kerra Holt has joined a band of Jedi volunteers traveling deep behind enemy lines, with no support from the Republic and little chance of survival. She thinks she is prepared for anything. She's wrong.
name: Aflame Part 1 of 5

description: Batman and Catwoman face off in the streets of Gotham City as they search for the ultimate weapon – a gun that never misses! Collecting BATMAN AND CATWOMAN: TRAIL OF THE GUN #1 and 2, this volume features the stunning artwork of superstar Ethan Van Sciver as he brings to life two of the most iconic characters in the DC Universe.

FIRST WAVE architect Brian Azzarello joins rising star Ivan Brandon for an epic journey to the Middle East, a land decimated by war - but still full of terrible secrets!

One of Doc's closest friends is lost among the shifting sands of the Forbidden Zone, and Doc'll have to fight his way through the Zone's battle-hardened inhabitants before he can come face-to-face (to face?) with the monster holding his ally captive: The Two Who Are One! And in the JUSTICE, INC. co-feature, Smitty is hot on the trail of the two-bit thug he's made the target of his bloodlust, but his tunnel vision is leading him into a dangerous trap...

And if the only light at the end of the tunnel is the Avenger, then there's no light in this world at all!
name: Into The Dark; Murder and Vengeance Part Two: It Takes One To Kill One
Huracàn Vs. las Drogas "la Cosa Nostra"

description: Can Jonah Hex help it if he's good at poker? No, of course not. But some people are sore losers - and sometimes those sore losers have some very rough and violent older brothers who are willing to fight for their little brother's honor...
name: Blood Lies Bleeding

description: The world Micah thought he knew is gone forever. But what has taken its place, and will he live to understand his new reality? Harlan Ellison's science-fiction masterpiece reaches its penultimate chapter!

When the most infamous villain in STAR TREK history is last seen in the Original Series episode 'Space Seed,' Khan Noonian Singh is an elegant, proud warrior-king. When he's next seen in STAR TREK II, he's a grizzled maniac, twisted by loss and an unquenchable thirst for revenge. What has happened between these two points in time to so radically alter what seemed to be an unbreakable will?

volume.name: Star Trek: Khan Ruling in Hell

name: A Punto de Perder la Màscara

description: Simon Pooni had it all going for him: plenty of friends at school, good looks, and his coach called him one of the most talented basketball players he's ever seen. But that was when he could still move his legs. Now he's living with multiple sclerosis, missing all the little things he used to take for granted, and escaping into the world of movies and comics with his best friend. Then... SUPERIOR entered his life.
name: One Magic Wish

description: The epic series by Mega-Talents ROGER LANGRIDGE and CHRIS SAMNEE continues! Thor tests his might against the strange and powerful (and slightly blue) SUB-MARINER. The God of Thunder vs. King of the Seven Seas, and YOU'VE got the front-row seat!
name: Thursday Morning

description:
It's the penultimate issue of 'The Death of Comic Book Guy!'

Marge believes that the Android's Dungeon may very well be haunted, while Lisa delves into the mysterious past of the Comic Book Guy, discovering his secret origin. Nelson finds a new purpose in life, the milkshake machine at the KrustyBurger gets clogged, and Bart 'fabricates' his grandest practical joke ever!
 
The Death of Comic Book Guy! Part 4 :

  • Chapter Nine: Who Ya Gonna Call?
  • Chapter Ten: Secret Origins
  • Chapter Eleven: Knit Happens!
  • Chapter Twelve: Game On!
  • Chapter Thirteen: Nerdier, She Wrote!
name: The Death of Comic Book Guy! Part 4

volume.name: Bongo Comics Presents: Comic Book Guy: The Comic Book

description:
Kit Walker finds the mercenaries in Bengali and about their suit that turns the one who is wearing invisible! He tracks each of them down and kills them, including the specific ones that killed his wife. There is blood bath and his apprentice Micheal gets killed. Kit then captures some of them to find out about who sent them to destroy his family and their motives.

With his family and his son killed and joined the ghosts of his forefathers, Kit could well be the only surviving Phantom.
name: Ghostwalk, Chapter Two: Ghost Hunters

description: Did you really think that Daken wouldn’t be involved in sending Wolverine’s soul to Hell? Now that his father is out of the way, Daken is free to do whatever he wants. And what does he want? EVERYTHING.
name: Empire, Pt. 2
And The Beast of the Woods
Family Affairs; A Trip To The Principal's Office!
It's My Party, And I'll Censored If I Want To! or What A Long, Strange Trip It's Been!!
Family Business or Hard At Work!
Here Come the Lovejoys... Manga-Style!; A Clockwork Lovejoy

description: By Tony Libido. In this final issue of the miniseries, the joyous moment arrives — Mildred has her baby! However, the lab results cast a shadow of some doubt about who the real father is! You'll enjoy Mildred's walk down memory lane as she tries to recall who might be another candidate for paternity. Meanwhile, Frank and Jenny are busy with activities of their own during "Father-Daughter Day" at Frank's office. Can they pull themselves out in time to witness the blessed event?

Some folks only pay lip service to family values. The Lovejoys, however, service every possible body part! In this brand new miniseries, Frank and Mildred's lovely daughter Debbie turns 18! The entire Lovejoy clan reunites to celebrate, including Frank's estranged stepdaughter Jenny and her husband Lloyd. Unfortunately, things turn sour when Jenny catches Lloyd and Debbie celebrating without their clothes on. Jenny decides to leave Lloyd, and make some changes in her life - which include finding her real father. The search will be costly, but stepdad Frank is willing to help...for a rather 'inappropriate' favor!

volume.name: Here Come The Lovejoys: Father Fixation

description: Frank offers daughter Debbie anything she desires for her birthday. It turns out that her heart's desire is breast augmentation. Since she's only 18, Frank must go along for guidance and support. Meanwhile, wife Mildred receives a dying request from one of her many stepfathers that puts her in a curious bind - literally! Stepdaughter Jenny's search for her real father proves problematic. Will Jenny agree to stepdad Frank's unthinkable terms to solve her problem? And, if she does, will Frank help pay for her inevitabe therapy bills? Stay tuned!

volume.name: Here Come The Lovejoys: Father Fixation

description: A sexy succubus visits the dreams of a warrior king with visions of S/M sex -- until he seeks her out in the flesh!
name: Sheedeva

description: By Dennis Cramer; reprinting Cramer's first six Eros comics, this book follows Mara as she journeys into her sister's depraved dreamworld to save her!
name: Mara Celtic Shamaness

description:
Back Blurb

Collecting all three of his previously released Eros Comix (Horny Toads, Pipsqueak Papers, and Malice in Wonderland) with bonus material -- much of it rare, if not impossible to find -- Naughty "Knotty" Woody is a delightful tribute to the lewd side of a legendary comics creator, Jam-packed with Wood's exceptional stylings (and plenty of sauce and spice!) Naughty "Knotty" Woody follows the master as he takes a satirical look at classic fantasy tales, twisting them and turning them upside down for a trip to worlds inverse and perverse!

In "Malice in Wonderland," out busty and lusty heroine takes a walk on the weird and wild side in a fantasyland where nothing makes sense, and sex is the rule -- one she's more than happy to follow!

Set in a forest fairyland, the "Pipsqueak Papers" tells the tale of impish Pip and his lust for the charming nymph Pip and his lust for the charming nymph Nudine -- and wait 'til you see what he does and where he goes to win her winsome charms!

In the "Wizard of Ooz," we take a trip down the yellow brick road -- only Dorothy is built like a brick shithouse and the road more traveled happens to run between her legs!

And that's not all! From "Strange Symphonies" and a "Brave Nude World" to the fanciful, outrageous spoofs of "Far-Out Fables" -- plus scads of saucy strips, pin-ups, sketchbook material and more! -- this edition makes a dazzling addition to the bookshelves of fans of humor, erotica and classic comics alike!
name: Naughty Knotty Wood

description: As this softcover collection definitively proves, proper bondage requires a German touch. Guenther and company deliver the tied and true goods every time in our most popular bondage title ever! This book collects the first eight issues of the comic book series, plus a sketchbook section and an all-new story in full color! Perversity and generosity in one whip-crackin' package -- need we say more?
name: Submissive Suzanne

description:
An anomaly causes an elderly mother to awake undressed inside a humid capsule. The voice of her daughter echoes in her memory, the intent of her words forgotten. Was she sharing the completeness of their unity, or hatefully wishing her mother's demise?

A seemingly infinite corridor of capsules hosts hundreds of persons, calmly sleeping, miserable underneath. Yet, an old man shares the mother's awareness, and is even certain of the nature of the place: a high-technology concentration camp; the second one for him to escape...
name: Misery Depot
Dental Men Prefer Blondes; I See London, I See France...; The Gay Divorcee Returns; Thumb Like It Hot
The Woman I Was Meant To Be; Perfect Service; Freaky Is Normal; Good Ol' Country Lovin'
Something In The Air; Service With A Smile; Too Deep To Quit; The Titty Twins
The Personal Assistant; A Cream Rinse To Remember; Time To Surrender To Desire; The Type Of Woman I Am

description: Psychologist Dr. Lester Horvath is a rising star in COBRA: he has developed a number scheme to categorize recruits, and its implementation has shaped COBRA into a well-oiled machine. Michael Monk is a failure-jobless, broke, on the verge of suicide. When a therapy test brings startling results, Dr. Horvath may suddenly have a purpose for Michael Monk...
name: Sedition by Numbers, Part 1

description:
STAN'S BACK! The Publishing Event of the Year! Stan Lee, the most colossal force in the history of comics, teams up with BOOM! Studios to deliver a brand new line of superhero comics!

The great innovator of our industry brings his inimitable talents back to the direct market in an explosive line of comics that nobody is prepared for!

In this first ongoing series, Soldier Zero, Stan teams up with critically acclaimed writer Paul Cornell (Action Comics, Doctor Who) and artist Javier Pina (Superman, Batman) for a dramatic, action-packed superhero scorcher.

When an alien parasite falls to Earth, wheelchair-bound college student Stewart Travers becomes infected, and goes through super-human changes that no mortal could imagine. Forced into a galactic war that's chosen Earth as the battlefield, Stewart defends the front line as Soldier Zero! Half-Human. Half-Alien. All Weapon.

The intergalactic war hits Earth this October in a new ongoing series from Stan Lee and BOOM! Studios! Featuring covers by fan-favorite artists Trevor Hairsine (X-Men), Dave Johnson (Punisher).
name: One Small Step For Man, Part One

description: Not enough DuckTales? Well get ready to reload as Scrooge, Launchpad and the rest of the Disney Afternoon ducks are back for a second arc! They've bested the blundering Beagle Boys and outfoxed the fearsome Flintheart; but who will triumph when they meet the menace of Magica de Spell? Only one place has the answer as BOOM Kids! invites you along as “Messes Become Successes!”
name: Lovelorn Launchpad; Double Indemnity
